title: Grateful Dead Live at San Francisco Civic Auditorium on 1984-12-29
lineage: Master Cassettes (Maxell Metalxial MX 90) Tascam 112MKII -> Korg MR-1, 1bit 2.8MHz -> USB -> Korg Audio Gate Software 24bit 96KHz -> Wave Lab 6.0 w/UAD -> R8brain for 16bit 44.1KHz sample rate conversion -> Traders Little Helper flac8 -> Tagged w/Tag & Rename
description:
Set 1

One More Saturday Night, Friend Of The Devil, My Brother Esau, Big Railroad Blues, Cassidy, Althea, Let It Grow

Set 2

Samson & Delilah-> Terrapin Station-> Playin' In The Band-> Drums-> Truckin'-> Stella Blue-> Not Fade Away-> E: Brokedown Palace

reviews.review_text: Nice AUD ...but could use a bit of pitch correction.  Cassidy sounds about a quarter tone sharp when compared to a 329.63 hertz E tone generated in Cool Edit.  Still, very clear and well-rounded recording.  Will likely add to gdluckynumbers.org.  Thanks!
hot songs just listen to stella blue. very good aud.
